{
  "query": "What is the evidence base for the effectiveness of creating large protrusions or ridges (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures?",
  "relevant_summary": "There is currently no evidence base for the effectiveness of creating large protrusions or ridges (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures, as no studies have directly evaluated these interventions [3443, 3445]. Action ID 3443 explicitly states that no studies were found that evaluated the effects of creating large protrusions on subtidal artificial structures on biodiversity during literature searches, leaving uncertainty about whether the intervention has desirable or harmful effects. Similarly, action ID 3445 confirms that no studies were found that evaluated the effects of creating large ridges or ledges on subtidal artificial structures on biodiversity. While no direct evidence exists for large features, there is limited evidence for similar smaller-scale interventions - action ID 3453 reports that one controlled study in Japan found mixed effects of creating small protrusions (1-50 mm) on subtidal structures, with macroalgal abundance varying by species. Action ID 3446 shows that one study in Italy found creating natural rocky reef topography on subtidal artificial structures did not increase juvenile canopy macroalgae abundance.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3443",
    "3445",
    "3453",
    "3446"
  ]
}

