{
  "query": "What factors influence the survival and growth of canopy algae transplanted onto subtidal artificial structures?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on the evidence from action documents, several factors influence the survival and growth of canopy algae transplanted onto subtidal artificial structures. Studies found that the presence of cages significantly affects both survival and growth - canopy algae showed increased cover when transplanted under cages but decreased when left uncaged. The mesh size of cages had no effect on growth, but wave exposure and surrounding habitat influenced survival. Surface orientation showed mixed effects - it influenced growth in some studies but had no effect on survival in others. Additionally, the distance from transplanted kelp individuals and surface orientation affected the abundance of kelp recruits. Some studies reported no survival of canopy algae transplants regardless of caging presence.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3471"
  ]
}

