{
  "query": "In northern Israel, how do the effects of creating pit habitats (1-50 mm) compare with creating hole habitats (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures?",
  "relevant_summary": "Both pit habitats (1-50 mm) and hole habitats (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures in northern Israel showed positive effects on biodiversity. For hole habitats (>50 mm), three studies found altered community composition and supported species absent from structures without habitat features, with two studies showing increased species richness/diversity. Effects on abundance were mixed - one study found increased brown crab abundance but no increase in other mobile invertebrates or fish abundance. For pit habitats (1-50 mm), one study found altered community composition, supported species absent from structures without habitat features, and increased species diversity, with mixed effects on abundances depending on species group. The evidence base is larger for hole habitats (3 studies) compared to pit habitats (1 study), but both showed generally positive effects on biodiversity in northern Israel.",
